               <msContents>
                  <summary>The Ms. contains only one text:&#xD;
I) Maṣḥafa gәṣṣawe, Lectionary for the first half of the year (fols. 5ra-200vc)&#xD;
I-1) Daily scriptural readings for the first half of the year (fols. 5ra-154vb)&#xD;
- Maskaram (1st month): fols. 5ra-8vc, 9ra-33ra &#xD;
- Ṭǝqǝmt (2nd month): fols. 33ra-52vc&#xD;
- Ḫǝdār (3rd month): fols. 52vc-80rb&#xD;
- Tāḫśāś (4th month): fols. 80rb-106rc&#xD;
- Ṭǝrr (5th month): fols. 106va-131rc&#xD;
- Yakkātit (6th month): fols 131rc-154vb&#xD;
I-2) Scriptural readings for Sundays, with Psalms (for the first half of the year) (fols. 154va-200vc)&#xD;
- Maskaram 1 to 8 (liturgical period called Yoḥannәs, “John the Forerunner”): fols. 154va-155vc;&#xD;
- Maskaram 8 (Zakāryās): fols. 155vc-156vb;&#xD;
- Maskaram 9 to 15 (liturgical period called Fәre,“the Fruits”): fols. 156vb-158ra;&#xD;
- Maskaram 16 (Ḥәnṣätä beta krәstiyan): fols. 158ra-159rb;&#xD;
- Maskaram 16 to 25 (liturgical period called Masqal, “the Cross”): fols. 159rb-161rc;&#xD;
- Maskaram 26 to Ḫǝdār 5 (liturgical period called Ṣәge, “the Flowers”): fols. 161rc-167ra;&#xD;
- Ḫǝdār 6 to Tāḫśāś 7 (liturgical period called ʾAstämḥәro, “the Supplication”): fols. 167ra-173r;&#xD;
- Sunday of the Preaching to the following Saturday (liturgical period called Sәbkät, “the Preaching”): fols. 173rc-174rc;&#xD;
- The following Sunday to the following Saturday (liturgical period called Bәrhan, “the Light”): fols. 174rc-175rb;&#xD;
- The following Sunday to Tāḫśāś 27 (Nolawi “the Sheperd”): fols. 175rb-176ra;&#xD;
- Tāḫśāś 28 (Märʿawi “the Bridegroom”): fols. 176ra-177ra;&#xD;
- Tāḫśāś 29 to Ṭǝrr 10 (Nazrәt, Ḫәḍnät) (liturgical period called Lәdät, “the Nativity”): fols-177ra-177vc;&#xD;
- The Eve of the Epiphany (Gähad) to the Sunday of the Encounter (Qäbbäla ṣom): fols. 177vc-197rb;&#xD;
- Fast of Nineveh (Nänäwe): fols. 197rb-197vc;&#xD;
- Fast of Heraclius (Ḥәrqal): fols. 197vc-198vc;&#xD;
- Monday, beginning of the Lent: fols. 198vc-200ra;&#xD;
- Friday, end of the Lent: fols. 200ra-200vc.</summary>
